Perfect—here’s a practical, non-technical Microsoft Dynamics 365 study plan designed specifically for a small business owner.
This focuses on using Dynamics to run your business better, not becoming an IT admin.

Microsoft Dynamics 365 Study Plan

For Small Business Owners

Time Commitment

30–60 minutes/day

4–6 weeks total

Focus: Sales, Customer Service, Finance, and automation

Phase 1: Dynamics 365 Basics (Week 1)

Goal: Understand what Dynamics can do for your business

Learn

What Dynamics 365 is (CRM + ERP)

Core apps overview:

Dynamics 365 Sales

Dynamics 365 Customer Service

Dynamics 365 Business Central
==========================
==============



How Dynamics connects with:

Outlook

Excel

Microsoft Teams

Hands-on

Sign up for a Dynamics 365 trial

Navigate dashboards and records

Explore sample data

$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$

Phase 2: Sales & Customer Management (Week 2)

Goal: Track leads, customers, and deals

Learn

Leads vs Contacts vs Accounts

Opportunities & sales pipelines

Activities (emails, calls, tasks)

Using Outlook integration

Hands-on

Enter real customers

Create a sales pipeline

Track follow-ups

Generate simple sales reports

Phase 3: Customer Service & Support (Week 3)

Goal: Improve customer experience & retention

Learn

Cases & queues

SLAs and response times

Knowledge base articles

Customer feedback tools

Hands-on

Create support tickets

Set up email-to-case

Build a simple knowledge article

Phase 4: Financials & Operations (Week 4)

Goal: Manage money, inventory, and operations
(Using Dynamics 365 Business Central)

Learn

Invoicing & billing

Payments & bank reconciliation

Inventory tracking

Vendors & purchasing

Hands-on

Create invoices

Track expenses

View profit & loss reports

Connect to Excel

Phase 5: Automation & Productivity (Week 5)

Goal: Save time with automation

Learn

Power Automate basics

Automated workflows:

Follow-up reminders

Lead assignment

Invoice notifications

Power Apps (basic understanding)

Hands-on

Automate lead follow-ups

Create approval workflows

Connect Dynamics with Outlook & Teams

Phase 6: Reporting & Decision Making (Week 6)

Goal: Use data to grow your business

Learn

Built-in reports & dashboards

KPIs (sales, customer retention, cash flow)

Power BI integration

Hands-on

Create a dashboard

Track monthly revenue

Analyze sales trends

What You Should Be Able to Do After This

✔ Track every customer interaction
✔ See sales pipelines clearly
✔ Automate repetitive tasks
✔ Improve customer support
✔ Make data-driven decisions

Recommended Learning Resources

Microsoft Learn (Dynamics 365 for Business Users)

Dynamics 365 YouTube demos

Built-in Dynamics guided tours

Power Platform tutorials

Business Owner Pro Tips

Start small—don’t enable everything at once

Use real business data while learning

Automate only after processes are clear

Review dashboards weekly

